name: 747 CARRYING A 787 ENGINE! National Airlines 747-400F at Calgary Airport
description:
On Thursday, August 24th, this Boeing 747-400 Freighter from National Airlines paid a visit to Calgary! It's not often we get to see 747s here in daylight, so this was a rare treat to see in some gorgeous evening sunlight.

As for why it was here, well there was nothing officially said, but they did load a General Electric GEnx engine, the type used on WestJet's Boeing 787s. 

It seems one of their Dreamliners flew into London-Heathrow on Tuesday, but its return flight was cancelled and it hasn't flown since. Seeing as this 747 spent about 4 hours on the ground here before departing for Heathrow, too, well, you can draw your own conclusions from there.

It was pretty cool to watch a big jet engine like that being loaded on a 747, which was no small undertaking. Enjoy this rare visitor with some unusual cargo!
